  "doc_id": "4673",
  "text": "However, there are two fundamental issues that cannot be overlooked in the IoMT. The first issue is the storage and management of data [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . For example, suppose a person wears a single pulse sensor that communicates hourly with a cloud storage database via the Low-Power WideArea Network (LPWAN). One thousand people would output 168,000 new data points per week. The volume of data even scales up dramatically with the increase number of sensors [CITATION_3] . Massive data may become a burden if it cannot be stored correctly and managed efficiently. Another issue is data integrity and confidentiality [CITATION_4] - [CITATION_5] . The data integrity is a basic premise, regardless of which platform provides storage services for these medical data. In addition, the data confidentiality is an important safeguard since medical data are very sensitive and contain inestimable commercial value.",
